Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['kɔ:sit]
*danh từ
 ■coocxê, áo nịt ngực (của đàn bà)

Anh - Anh
corset
■ noun a woman's tightly fitting undergarment extending from below the chest to the hips, worn to shape the figure.
⁃ a similar garment worn to support a weak or injured back.
⁃ historical a tightly fitting laced or stiffened outer bodice or dress.
Derivatives
corsetedadjective
corsetrynoun
Origin
ME: from OFr., dimin. of cors 'body', from L. corpus.

Từ điển Đồng nghĩa
corset
▸ noun GIRDLE, panty girdle, foundation (garment), corselette; Brit. roll-on; informal, dated waspie; historical stays.
